=Description=

"THE PUBLIC SCHOOL project was initiated in New York by common room and Telic Arts Exchange as The Public School (for Architecture) and operated with support from the Van Alen Institute between September and December 2009.

In January 2010 THE PUBLIC SCHOOL continued as THE PUBLIC SCHOOL NEW YORK based at 177 Livingston Street, Brooklyn, NY 11201.

Beginning November 1, 2010, THE PUBLIC SCHOOL NEW YORK will meet at itinerant locations throughout the five boroughs. Consult individual course listings for locations.

In September 2011, THE PUBLIC SCHOOL NEW YORK will begin operating out of its new home at 155 Freeman Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11222.

THE PUBLIC SCHOOL is a self-organizing educational program for which the curriculum is proposed by the general public. The development of course topics and class participation is open to students and instructors from any field of study."
(http://nyc.thepublicschool.org/about)


